---
import { getCollection } from 'astro:content';
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';

const projects = (await getCollection('projects')).sort((a, b) => a.data.order - b.data.order);
---

<Base title="Saurabh Johri">
	<header>
		<h1>Saurabh Johri</h1>
		<p class="muted tagline">Software engineer. Django &amp; Go on education platforms.</p>
		<p class="links">
			<a href="/resume.pdf">Resume (PDF)</a>
			<a href="https://github.com/s-johri">GitHub</a>
			<a href="https://linkedin.com/in/saurabh-j-49bb87ba">LinkedIn</a>
		</p>
	</header>

	<section id="about" class="reveal section">
		<h2 class="section-label">About</h2>
		<div>
			<p>
				Software engineer with an MS in Artificial Intelligence from Boston University and ~2 years
				at Code Argo, building education-platform software for the BITS Pilani ecosystem that serves
				around 180,000 users. Full-stack across Python/Django and Go, spanning student-portal features,
				certificate-generation microservices, data pipelines, and backend proxies, with an
				AI-assisted development workflow. I like owning systems end-to-end, from frontend UX down to
				the Go services underneath, and shipping features that hold up at real scale. Open-source
				contributor to <a href="https://github.com/signintech/gopdf">gopdf</a>, a ~2,900-star Go PDF
				library.
			</p>
		</div>
	</section>

	<section id="experience" class="reveal section">
		<h2 class="section-label">Experience</h2>
		<article>
			<div class="role">
				<h3>Software Engineer, Code Argo</h3>
				<span class="dates">May 2024 &ndash; Present</span>
			</div>
			<p class="muted org">Vendor engineering team for the BITS Pilani ecosystem &middot; Remote</p>
			<ul>
				<li>
					Lead ongoing feature development on <strong>elearn</strong>, a Django student portal with
					<strong>~180,000 total users</strong> (~75,000 active students); owned frontend development end-to-end
					early in the engagement. Built an async/streaming CSV export for large MGPA and
					student-evaluation datasets, scaling the export limit to <strong>2.5M rows</strong>, and
					shipped superuser impersonation (&ldquo;Log in as&rdquo;) with full audit logging.
				</li>
				<li>
					Maintain and extend <strong>elearn-api-proxy</strong> (Go), a certificate/transcript
					generation service pulling program, degree, and division data from an ERP
					student-status API, with <strong>52,000+ certificates and transcripts generated</strong>
					to date for elearn's student body.
				</li>
				<li>
					Built <strong>attendance-sync</strong> (Go), a daily cron service parsing
					course-meeting attendance dumps from a Microsoft API and forwarding organizer
					attendance and role data into elearn, with
					<strong>1.3M+ attendance records processed</strong> to date.
				</li>
				<li>
					Built <strong>discordbot-go</strong>, a Discord/Google account-linking gate bot
					serving a community of <strong>~250 members</strong>; implemented a
					reconciliation/self-healing sweep to correct membership drift and migrated identity
					and cohort-channel storage from local JSON to PostgreSQL, then to Valkey/Redis.
				</li>
				<li>
					Co-built <strong>argo-api-proxy</strong> (Go/Fiber) with API-key request
					authentication, config-driven routing, and hot config reload; replaced in-memory
					query buffering with streamed response execution.
				</li>
			</ul>
		</article>
	</section>

	<section id="projects" class="reveal section">
		<h2 class="section-label">Projects</h2>
		<ul class="project-list">
			{projects.map((project) => (
				<li>
					<div class="project-title">
						<a href={`/projects/${project.id}`}>{project.data.title}</a>
						<span class="badge">{project.data.kind === 'case-study' ? 'Case study' : 'Open source'}</span>
					</div>
					<p class="muted">{project.data.summary}</p>
				</li>
			))}
		</ul>
	</section>
</Base>

<style>
	.tagline {
		margin: 0 0 1.25rem;
		font-size: 1.1rem;
	}
	.links {
		display: flex;
		flex-wrap: wrap;
		gap: 1.5rem;
		margin: 0;
		font-family: var(--mono);
		font-size: 0.8rem;
		letter-spacing: 0.02em;
	}
	.role {
		display: flex;
		flex-wrap: wrap;
		align-items: baseline;
		justify-content: space-between;
		gap: 0.25rem 1rem;
	}
	.role h3 {
		margin: 0;
	}
	.dates {
		font-family: var(--mono);
		font-size: 0.75rem;
		color: var(--muted);
		white-space: nowrap;
	}
	.org {
		margin: 0.25rem 0 1rem;
	}
	.project-list {
		list-style: none;
		padding: 0;
		margin: 0;
	}
	.project-list li {
		margin: 0;
		padding: 1.1rem 0;
	}
	.project-list li + li {
		border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
	}
	.project-list li:first-child {
		padding-top: 0;
	}
	.project-title {
		display: flex;
		flex-wrap: wrap;
		align-items: baseline;
		gap: 0.6rem;
	}
	.project-title a {
		font-weight: 600;
	}
	.project-list p {
		margin: 0.35rem 0 0;
		font-size: 0.95rem;
	}
</style>
